<paragraph blockId="2.[140,1108,729,897]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[140,388,729,756]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis box="[140,282,729,755]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" reason="1">Description</emphasis>
of male.
</emphasis>
Length including forewings in repose 8.0 mm, width between humeral angles 
<quantity box="[315,408,765,791]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" unit="mm" value="4.6">4.6 mm</quantity>
. Color. Head yellow-orange. Pronotum yellow-orange dorsally and posteriorly, yellow laterally except with large lateral indentation at mid-length black. Forewing fuscous at coriaceous base and transversally at distal crossveins, cells tinted yellow basally, hyaline distally. Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[759,856,870,897]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="2.[140,184,1558,1580]" captionTargetBox="[140,1108,971,1538]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[140,1108,970,1538]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-6. Smilirhexia naranja, sp. n. 1-3, Lateral, dorsal, and anterior views of head, pronotum, wings, and legs (forewing anterior apices presumably rolled inward as a preservative side-effect). 4, Lateral view, cleared terminalia before dissection. 5-6. Aedeagus in lateral and anterior views, respectively. aed, aedeagus; lp, unarmed lateral plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3778974" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3778974/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">Figs 4-6</figureCitation>
): lateral plate distinct,
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3778974" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3778974" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3778974/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" startId="2.[140,184,1558,1580]" targetBox="[140,1108,971,1538]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[140,1108,1558,1676]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[140,233,1558,1580]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">Figs 1-6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="McKamey, 2008" authorityName="McKamey" authorityYear="2008" box="[240,420,1558,1580]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Smilirhexia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="naranja" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[240,420,1558,1580]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">Smilirhexia naranja</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[432,484,1559,1580]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
1-3, Lateral, dorsal, and anterior views of head, pronotum, wings, and legs (forewing anterior apices presumably rolled inward as a preservative side-effect). 4, Lateral view, cleared terminalia before dissection. 5-6. Aedeagus in lateral and anterior views, respectively. 
<emphasis box="[1006,1036,1622,1643]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">aed</emphasis>
, aedeagus; 
<emphasis box="[183,200,1654,1675]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">lp</emphasis>
, unarmed lateral plate.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[140,1108,166,862]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
long, lacking protuberances. Aedeagus narrow in anterior view, in lateral view Ushaped and widest at mid-length, anterior margin with many denticulae of increasing size ventrally; styles simple, distally recurved (
<figureCitation box="[654,723,237,263]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="2.[140,184,1558,1580]" captionTargetBox="[140,1108,971,1538]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[140,1108,970,1538]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-6. Smilirhexia naranja, sp. n. 1-3, Lateral, dorsal, and anterior views of head, pronotum, wings, and legs (forewing anterior apices presumably rolled inward as a preservative side-effect). 4, Lateral view, cleared terminalia before dissection. 5-6. Aedeagus in lateral and anterior views, respectively. aed, aedeagus; lp, unarmed lateral plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3778974" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3778974/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), apex acute.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[140,1108,166,862]" box="[185,407,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,277,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis box="[185,272,272,298]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" reason="1">Female</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
